info.other:
I included “England” in Site address to be consistent with other cards. Georef not working for me. The stuff in Surface looks as though some of it should perhaps be in Description & Patina fields.  There's lots more detail on the back of the card - see below. Bottom left of card says "MJR". There's quite a lot written beside diagram, but bits of it are missing from this copy. Note 1 - I think a first Heading might have been "BLADE", but that it has been cut off in the copying process. I'm Not sure if the second heading is RIDGE, or whether a "B" has been cut off and it should be BRIDGE. Note 2 - I presume some of the para. nos. have also been chopped off in the copying process, but context indicates what they must be. I have put the missing paragraph numbers back in or it won't make sense. It all reads as follows:
"1) Blade body short and [...] sided. Almost square. Curves sharply out to blade edge.[;] 2) Marked recurved wings[;]3) presence of bevel - high [...] on blade face c. 2.6 cms from edge[;]4) Blade section - rectangular[;]5)  Sides squared[;]6)No signs of hammerwork[;]RIDGE:[;] 1) Hammered feature having been raised up under the flanges[;]2) Raised level (bevel?) with flanges, which are bent over the ends of the stop.[;]3 Stop is at an angle, sloping in towards septum. St. face to septum.[;]4)Bevelled top with straight face to blade.[;]5) Socket shape rectang, with inturned flanges giving it a waisted appearance.[;]6) flat floor to socket with [...]-sided inturned flanges[;]7) Flanges: a) leaf-shaped, extending for c. 1cm below stop. Hammered down. b) Flanges are slightly faceted along the inbent edges[;]CONDITION: Blade edge shattered, surface pitting extensive[;]PATINA: dark brown. shows signs of rust patina."

info.description: Dimensions: L 137.2mm; We 73.7mm; Wst 29.2mm; Wbt. 19.5mm; Lhaft 62 and 63; Bfg 15.8mm; Hfg 3.5mm; Tst 12.8mm; Tbt 1.5mm (undam part); Tebev. 8.5 and 11.0mm; Debev 16.5 & 28mm[;]Typology: stop a rounded bump in profile; slightly curved on both faces; defined furrow on one blade face only - on reverse hollowing in this position but no delineated lower bevel; fgs. overlapping along haft end; possible longitud. facets on upper sides - v. faint indications; no bl. tip hollows or butt groove; cross-section of lower body with swollen faces.[;]Manufacture: v. diffuse hmks. on bl. face - more on reverse showing; deliberate embellishment of lower sides; asym. of cutting edge could have been enhanced/created by reworking of broken tip.[;]Condition: squared bl. tip with smoothed hammered surface same colour as rest - small crack in it suggests likely re-shaping after breaking e.; score across one flange not modern; edge not sharp and v. little serrated; butt hammered, prob. recent forming partial and v. slight lipping; series of scmks. along body & diag. on sides (rev.) and across c. e. - prob. all from modern cleaning.

info.description: Typology: Stop a rounded bump in profile; slightly curved on both faces; defined furrows on one blade face only - on reverse hollowing in this position, but no delineated lower bevel; fgs. overhang along haft end; possible logitud. facets on uppersides - v. faint indications; No bl. tip hollows or butt groove; cross-section of lower body with swollen faces.[;]Manufacture: v. diffuse hmks. on bl. face -more on reverse showing; deliberate embellishment of lower sides; asym. of cutting edge could have been enhanced/created by re-working of broken tip[;]Condition: squared bl. tip with smooth hammered surface same colour as rest - small crack in it suggests likely re-shaping after breakage; score across one flange not modern; edge not sharp and v. little serrated; butt hammered, prob. recent, forming partial & v. slight lipping; series of scmks. along body and diag. on side (rev.) & across c.e. - probably from modern cleaning

info.description: Dimensions: EL 115mm; EWe 33.2; Tbt (centre) 3.5mm; Tbl 13.8mm; minTsep 4.3mm; maxEHfg 14mm; Wt 212.56 g.[;]Typology: cutting e. bevelled, but no distinct line; "V" end to septums; central butt notch with rough sur., one intact corner prong folded over - flat top; bevels on sides at wing/bt. junction; sl. bev. at top of sep.[;]Manufacture: cg. gl. around lp. only; bl. tip hollows - bl. sides sl. concave up to wgs; no obvious hmks or gmks at edge;  hmks in one sep. - manuf. or mutilation?[;]Condition: one bt. prong, 3 wing ends, + past of fourth, all broken off in antiquity; surviving wing battered by hmks - anc. dam.; lp squashed to one side; virt. all of edge chipped - one very small part poss. on orig. line.[;]Attached Material: some fawn soil under wing
